|User Interface:

 

Please follow the following links: http://annotation4mt.hopto.org/

 

The html page will contain a set of links for a subset of images. Once you click on the desired link.

The number near the link contains the number of litter items detected and tagged within that image. Choose a link with ‘0’ litter items.

 

Follow these three steps

 

Step 1: Select “Bounding Box” annotation method

Step 2: Search and annotate objects within images

Step 3: When ready with the image select Next Image and repeat Step 2:

 

Important:

 Choose a random link from the list with 0 tagged items.

 If you find the image has already been tagged move to the next image.

 

 

 

Annotation Instructions:

 

There are a number of images with litter, though not all images contain objects.

 

Litter is usually defined as objects that can be thrown away by people. Very heavy objects are not be tagged as litter.

 

Some notes on the annotation process:

 

  1. 1.A bounding box needs to put around the required object, 

     

 

  1. 2.Litter object/s are very small so zooming would be necessary, 

 

  1.  

    Some litter will be hard to find .

 

  1.  

     

     

 

 

  1. 3.Each object needs to be annotated separately except for shards and very small items, 

 

  1. Very small items near each other can be tagged in a group.

     

    The oil tank is not considered litter as it cannot be thrown away.

 

 

 

 

 Shards of pottery.

 

 

 

 

 

 

  1. 4.Only objects that are confidently litter will be tagged. Even though the shape is not recognizable, 

 

 

 

  1. 5.Litter can be truncated, 

 

  1. 6.Litter can be occluded, 

 

  1. 7.There are different types of litter, 

     
     
 

          Plastic Bottles           Aluminum Cans          Rusted items                Plastic Bags

 

 

 

      Glass Bottles         General Litter             Disposable Cutlery   Paper

 

     Cartons  Pipes

 

Not to be considered litter :

  • •normal terrain,  

  • •vegetation,  

  • •roads,  

  • •construction,  

  • •cars,  

  • •people ,  

  • •signs,  

  • •poles, and  

  • •wood. 

However litter on the items above should be tagged normally.
